      </userestrict>
      <bioghist id="aspace_cc3a513eddf5dd84cb898a9b759532fc">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>John Lewis Gaddis was born in Cotulla, Texas in 1941. Gaddis received his B.A., M.A., and Ph.D. from the University of Texas, Austin in 1963, 1965, and 1968, respectively. After earning his Ph.D., Gaddis taught history at Ohio University for 28 years. In 1997, Gaddis became the Robert A. Lovett Professor of Military and Naval History at Yale University. His primary areas of scholarly research and teaching are the Cold War and grand strategy, subjects on which he has authored multiple books. His biography of United States diplomat George F. Kennan, <title>
               <part>George F. Kennan: An American Life</part>
            </title>, won the 2012 Pulitzer Prize for Biography or Autobiography.</p>  
      </bioghist>
